															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/soullesssingularity" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(637830); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=637830&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610183077" alt="SoullessSingularity" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=637830)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/soullesssingularity" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(637830); return false;" >SoullessSingularity</a></span> <span class="odate time_1347412499 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">12 Sep 2012 01:14</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1562552">
									

<p>Feeling bad I had to do this to Gears of all people.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>A trashed-out storefront, it bore the distinction of being across the street from a hidden Church meeting point.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I don't understand this sentence at all. Do you mean the storefront bore the distinction? Why not 'A trashed-out storefront bore the distinction..'?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>slipped away with feline suppleness</p>
</blockquote>
<p>This phrase also seems really off to me, for some reason. 'with feline suppleness' as a turn of phrase seems really&#8230; eh, to me&#8230; I guess</p>
<blockquote>
<p>which I am varying degrees of proud and ashamed of. The CIA came knocking one day, promised all the James Bond shit.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>In my head, the guy that says '&#8230;which I am varying degrees of proud and ashamed of' is not the same guy that says 'James Bond shit'. It just is odd to me.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>We didn't do a lot of direct scp-related stuff<br />
Had a report of a SCP escape</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I'm rather confused as to why there's this inconsistency.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Harken's hand curled, nails pushing against his skull, holding for a few seconds, twitching, before he lowered it again, eyes returning fixedly to his shoes.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>The comma spam bugs me here. Don't know if it's all good grammar and all that though, so more of a personal quibble than much else.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>“I heard them dieing.”</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I'm pretty sure it's dying.</p>
<p>Small things that kind of ruined it for me. Also Harken's ranting near the end got a bit narmy for me. I really wish I could like it,y'know, because it's you (Gears) and all. I'm sorry.</p>

							</div>

										<div class="signature">
					<hr class="signature-separator"/>
					

<p>Living the dream, or dreaming the life?</p>

				</div>
					
					
