					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dr-gears" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(172464); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=172464&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610183077" alt="Dr Gears" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=172464)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dr-gears" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(172464); return false;" >Dr Gears</a></span> <span class="odate time_1347413189 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">12 Sep 2012 01:26</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1562558">
									

<p>Thanks for being honest, I'd rather that then anything else. I'll try and address some of these issues soon.</p>
<p>(Edit) And now it's soon!</p>
<hr />
<p>Fixed a couple spelling issues, as i am the worst proofreader you will ever see, ever. A lot of the other formatting things and other odd turns of phrase are just&#8230;i guess a sort of written mental tick. I have a thing for &quot;&#8230;&quot; as well, it seems. Sorry if it's a bit jarring, but i do try and make things more sane for the general public.</p>
<hr />
<p>As for this:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>We didn't do a lot of direct scp-related stuff<br />
Had a report of a SCP escape</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Harken's old team honestly didn't handle a lot of direct SCP stuff. They came either before or after the screaming and pain, not during. When the 106 thing happened, they had the luck of being the closest team able to respond. Just bad luck of the draw.</p>
<hr />
<p>Harken being odd/narmy/inconsistent:</p>
<p>Harken really, really wants to be a bastard. He wants to be this cold, snide, aloof asshole who just moves through life. The Watchman's Comedian is probably his hero, if he would admit to such a thing. In reality, it's all a mask, at best. He puts on a show to make people either ignore him, or dislike him. However, his gooey, insecure, screwed-up center shows through sometimes. Harken isn't supposed to make you go &quot;wow, what a cool guy!&quot;, it's more &quot;Wow, that dude is fucked up.&quot;</p>

							</div>

								
